Weight loss starts with starting.

Twalk is a friendly, science-backed nudge service for weight-loss actions, delivered in iPhone Messages. No dashboards. No streak guilt. Just gentle prompts that help you take the next tiny step.

Evidence

Texts can 2x outcomes. Incentives can amplify that.

Your brain wants comfort now. Weight loss pays later. Twalk bridges the gap with friendly, science-backed messages that make the next step feel small and doable. Heres a taste of whats inside:

Hyperbolic Discounting

Your brain thinks future you will handle it. Twalk turns later into now, with micro-steps you can actually do.

The Zeigarnik Effect

Unfinished intentions stick around. Twalk nudges you to close the loop with one small action, so it stops buzzing in your head.

Social Accountability

Implementation Intentions

Vague plans fail. Twalk turns I should into At 7:30, Ill and texts you at the moment youre most likely to follow through.

The 2x better channel proof (large RCT, men with obesity)

2.1more weight loss vs control

In Game of Stones, texting alone achieved 2.7% mean weight change at 12 months vs 1.3% in control. That is roughly 2.1 more loss than control.

3.7with loss-framed endowment incentives

Even stronger: texting + loss-framed endowment incentives reached 4.8% vs 1.3% control, about 3.7 the control outcome (and 5.7 kg vs 1.5 kg).

Translation: the channel can double outcomes, and incentive design can materially amplify it.

The leaderboard of effects Twalk prioritizes

Where the hardest evidence is strongest:

  • Integrated nudge strategies (25 RCTs): 0.96 kg average effect on body weight.
  • Financial incentives (meta-analysis, objective outcomes): 2.36 kg more lost vs control.
  • Men with obesity (large RCT): 5.7 kg (texts + incentives) vs 1.5 kg control at 12 months.

How it works

Simply supportive.
Twalk keeps it light: no giant plan to fail, just the next small action that moves the needle.

Starting is the hard part. So we design for starts.
You do not fail weight loss. Your brain just keeps choosing later because later feels cheaper. Twalk is built for the moment where plans collapse into procrastination.

Right-time nudges

Prompts arrive when youre most likely to act, not when youre asleep or stressed.

Micro-steps

Shoes on beats work out. Tiny starts reduce friction and make follow-through easier.

Science in plain language

Built from behavior research on present bias, prompts, and implementation cues.

iPhone Messages only

No new app to get used to. Twalk lives where you already look, dozens of times per day. (And yes, that is the point.)

Support

Simple by design. Honest about the hard parts.

Twalk does not promise magic. It promises fewer I will start Monday loops. You keep control. The system keeps the spark alive until action happens.

What Twalk is

  • A prompt pipeline that adapts nudges to your behavior
  • Designed around proven biases: present-bias, inertia, loss aversion
  • Built for weight loss starts, not perfect tracking

What Twalk is not

  • A calorie counter
  • A social media feed
  • A guilt machine

References for the evidence section
1) Hoddinott et al. Text Messages With Financial Incentives for Men With Obesity, JAMA (Game of Stones trial). Key outcomes at 12 months: 4.8% (texts + incentives) vs 2.7% (texts) vs 1.3% (control); and 5.7 kg vs 3.0 kg vs 1.5 kg.
2) Gong et al. Financial incentives for objectively-measured physical activity or weight loss PLOS ONE (2018). Meta-analysis: 2.36 kg more lost vs control (objective outcomes).
3) The nudge strategies for weight loss in adults with obesity and overweight (systematic review/meta-analysis; 25 RCTs): 0.96 kg average weight reduction.
